<Docs title="Composition root" description="One file that wires everything." eyebrow="Pattern">
  <p><strong>Where:</strong> <code>src/composition.ts</code>.</p>
  <p>
    <strong>The rule:</strong> all <code>new Service(...)</code> calls happen here. Every
    other file receives dependencies.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Why:</strong> grepability. "Where does this service come from?" has one
    answer. Swapping implementations is a one-file change.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Reading:</strong> Mark Seemann, <em>Dependency Injection Principles, Practices,
    and Patterns</em> (ch. 4).
  </p>
  <p>See <a href="/concepts/composition-root/">Composition root concept</a> for more.</p>
</Docs>
